Path: godot/tutorials/platform/ios/plugins_for_ios.rst
Summary: This section describes the Store Kit API for in-app purchases in Godot on iOS.

The Store Kit API is accessible through the InAppStore singleton, which is initialized automatically.

The following methods are available:

Method: purchase(params) → Error
Method: request_product_info(params) → Error
Method: restore_purchases() → Error
Method: set_auto_finish_transaction(enable: bool) → void
Method: finish_transaction(product_id: String) → void

The pending events interface includes:

Method: get_pending_event_count() → int
Method: pop_pending_event() → Variant
---CHUNK---
Document: plugins_for_ios.rst
Path: godot/tutorials/platform/ios/plugins_for_ios.rst
Summary: Describes the `purchase` method for handling in-app purchases in iOS plugins.
purchase Purchases a product ID through the Store Kit API. You have to call finish_transaction(product_id) once you receive a successful response or call set_auto_finish_transaction(true) prior to calling purchase(). These two methods ensure the transaction is completed.
---CHUNK---
Document: plugins_for_ios.rst
Path: godot/tutorials/platform/ios/plugins_for_ios.rst
Summary: Describes how to pass parameters to the in-app purchase purchase method.
Parameters
Takes a dictionary as a parameter, with one field, product_id, a string with your product ID. Example:

GDScript:
    var result = in_app_store.purchase({ "product_id": "my_product" })
---CHUNK---
Document: plugins_for_ios.rst
Path: godot/tutorials/platform/ios/plugins_for_ios.rst
Summary: Describes the structure of response events for in-app purchases in iOS plugins.
The response event will be a dictionary with the following fields:

On error:
GDScript:
    {
      "type": "purchase",
      "result": "error",
      "product_id": "the product ID requested",
    }

On success:
GDScript:
    {
      "type": "purchase",
      "result": "ok",
      "product_id": "the product ID requested",
    }
---CHUNK---
