---CHUNK---
Document: plugins_for_ios.rst
Path: godot/tutorials/platform/ios/plugins_for_ios.rst
Summary: Describes how to pass product IDs to the in-app store for requesting product information.
Parameters
Takes a dictionary as a parameter, with a single product_ids key to which a string array of product IDs is assigned. Example:
GDScript:
    var result = in_app_store.request_product_info({ "product_ids": ["my_product1", "my_product2"] })
---CHUNK---
Document: plugins_for_ios.rst
Path: godot/tutorials/platform/ios/plugins_for_ios.rst
Summary: Describes the structure of the response event dictionary for product information requests in iOS plugins.
The response event will be a dictionary with the following fields:
{
  "type": "product_info",
  "result": "ok",
  "invalid_ids": [ list of requested IDs that were invalid ],
  "ids": [ list of IDs that were valid ],
  "titles": [ list of valid product titles (corresponds with list of valid IDs) ],
  "descriptions": [ list of valid product descriptions ],
  "prices": [ list of valid product prices ],
  "localized_prices": [ list of valid product localized prices ],
}
---CHUNK---
